    </header>

    <section>
      {{! template-lint-disable "no-duplicate-landmark-elements" }}
      <header>
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
      </header>
      <p>One of the backbone technologies we use at
        <a href='https://redpencil.io/'>redpencil.io</a>
        is SPARQL, a W3C standard designed for querying RDF graphs. It is
        the main way in which we interact with data, and we firmly believe
        that having a good grasp of how it works, whether you are a
        technical person or not, will be very helpful! For that reason,
        we've written this tutorial to guide you through SPARQL, it's
        syntax, subtleties, and everything in between.</p>

    </section>

    <section>
      {{! template-lint-disable "no-duplicate-landmark-elements" }}
      <header>
        <h2>Setup</h2>
      </header>
      <p>
        This tutorial is fully interactive from your web browser. We use
        <a href='https://triply.cc/docs/yasgui'>Yasgui</a>
        to interact with our SPARQL data, each exercise has an embedded
        console you can use to query our data. The code for this tutorial is
        hosted
        <a href='#'>here</a>, so if you prefer you can run it on your own
        machine.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      {{! template-lint-disable "no-duplicate-landmark-elements" }}
      <header>
        <h2>References</h2>
      </header>
      <p>
        This tutorial is in large part based upon a number of slide decks
        available
        <a href='#'>here</a>. If you want more in-depth information about
        SPARQL, we highly recommend the following resources:

        <ul>
          <li>The
            <a href='https://www.w3.org/TR/sparql11-overview/'>SPARQL 1.1
              W3C specification</a>. This document defines the syntax,
            semantics and features of SPARQL</li>
          <li><a
            href='https://www.w3.org/2004/Talks/17Dec-sparql/intro/all.html'
          >Introduction to RDF Query with SPARQL. Part 1 - Introduction</a></li>
          <li><a href='http://learningsparql.com/'>Learning SPARQL book</a></li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </section>

